 our computations show that if the\nprimordial radiation field is described by a pure blackbody, then there is no\nsignificant emission from any hydrogen transition at redshifts greater than $z\n\\sim 2000$. This is in contrast to some earlier works, where the existence of a\n`pre-recombination' peak was claimed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 17 Jul 2006 12:06:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
