{"id":"quant-ph/0607110","submitter":"Lajos Di\\'osi","authors":"Lajos Di\\'osi","title":"Notes on Certain Newton Gravity Mechanisms of Wave Function Localisation\n  and Decoherence","comments":"8pp LaTex, Submitted to J. Phys. A: Math-Gen, for the special issue\n  ``The Quantum Universe'' in honor of G. C. Ghirardi","journal-ref":"J.Phys. A40 (2007) 2989-2995","doi":"10.1088/1751-8113/40/12/S07","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  Both the additional non-linear term in the Schr\\\"odinger equation and the\nadditional non-Hamiltonian term in the von Neumann equation, proposed to ensure\nlocalisation and decoherence of macro-objects, resp., contain the same\nNewtonian interaction potential formally. We discuss certain aspects that are\ncommon for both equations. In particular, we calculate the enhancement of the\nproposed localisation and/or decoherence effects, which would take place if one\ncould lower the conventional length-cutoff and resolve the mass density on the\ninteratomic scale.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 17 Jul 2006 15:47:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
